  "texts": [
    "DP can be divided into global differential privacy (GDP) and local differential privacy (LDP).",
    "GDP adds noise to the output of queries over the entire dataset, whereas LDP adds noise to each individual's data prior to any analysis.",
    "It is appropriate to note that the boundary between differential privacy and cryptographic techniques (Sect. 2.4.3) is also not strict.",
    "Cryptographic algorithms are often applied to implement differential privacy.",
    "Homomorphic Encryption (HE) is a cryptography paradigm that allows computation to be performed on encrypted data."
  ],
